- 2.0.2 | Feb 25 2026:

  -- New Features --

[New] SYN flood protection: SYNFLOOD chain rate-limits inbound TCP SYN packets
      via iptables limit module; configurable rate/burst thresholds, LOG +
      DROP for excess, dual-stack support
[New] SMTP outbound blocking: SMTP_BLOCK restricts outbound SMTP (ports 25,
      465, 587) to whitelisted users/groups; root always allowed;
      SMTP_ALLOWUSER/SMTP_ALLOWGROUP exemptions with runtime --gid-owner
      detection; works independently of EGF toggle
[New] Temporary allow/deny with per-entry TTL: apf -ta/-td HOST TTL adds
      time-limited trust entries; supports seconds/minutes/hours/days (300,
      5m, 1h, 7d); automatic cron expiry; list with --templ, flush with
      --tempf; block escalation auto-promotes repeat temp denies to permanent
      via PERMBLOCK_COUNT/PERMBLOCK_INTERVAL
[New] Custom hook scripts: hook_pre.sh/hook_post.sh sourced before/after
      iptables rules; activated by chmod 750; all APF variables available;
      preserved across upgrades
[New] Silent IP blocking: silent_ips.rules drops all traffic to/from listed
      addresses with no logging; IPv4/IPv6 supported; entries validated with
      valid_host(); preserved across upgrades
[New] Search CLI: apf -g PATTERN searches iptables rules (IPv4/IPv6), ipset
      sets, and trust files; case-insensitive
[New] Per-port connection limiting via xt_connlimit: IG_TCP_CLIMIT and
      IG_UDP_CLIMIT config variables with port:limit pairs, port range
      support, and VNET per-IP binding
[New] ipset 7-field format: per-list refresh interval and max entry count;
      IPSET_REFRESH global default; per-list interval tracking via
      .ipset.timestamps; backward-compatible auto-migration from 4-field
      and 5-field formats
[New] download_url(): unified download helper with curl primary, wget
      fallback; redirect following, 10s connect / 60s total timeout, 3
      retries; all download sites migrated; check_deps() warns when
      neither available
[New] Advanced trust syntax in CLI: apf -a/-d/-ta/-td/-u now accept
      proto:flow:port:ip format (e.g., "tcp:in:d=22:s=10.0.0.0/8") for
      protocol/direction/port-scoped trust rules; live iptables insertion
      via trust_entry_rule(); bare IP removal also removes advanced entries
      containing that IP; duplicate detection, IPv6 bracket syntax, port
      ranges, and temp trust TTL markers all supported
[New] validate_config(): startup config validation covers stop targets,
      rate/burst formats, connlimit syntax, SYSCTL_SYNCOOKIES conflict,
      IFACE_UNTRUSTED, RAB_PSCAN_LEVEL/HITCOUNT/TIMER, LOG_LEVEL/TARGET/RATE,
      ICMP_LIM, SET_EXPIRE, FQDN_TIMEOUT, SET_REFRESH,
      PERMBLOCK_COUNT/INTERVAL, and SYSCTL_CONNTRACK; clear error messages
      instead of cryptic iptables failures
[New] FQDN pre-resolution in trust system: hostnames are resolved to IP
      addresses via getent before loading into iptables; supports multiple
      A/AAAA records, IPv6 (when USE_IPV6=1), configurable timeout via
      FQDN_TIMEOUT; resolved= metadata in trust file comments enables
      removal without DNS; refresh (apf -e) re-resolves FQDNs; works in
      CLI (-a/-d/-ta/-td/-u) and bulk load
[New] --rules: dump active iptables rules to stdout for piping/scripting;
      uses -S format consistent across nft/legacy backends; includes IPv6
      when USE_IPV6=1
[New] --info: firewall status summary with sections for status (active state,
      rules, chains), trust system (allow/deny/temp counts, ban expiry, block
      escalation, FQDN resolution), filtering (stop targets, inbound/outbound
      ports, packet sanity, connlimit, SYN flood, SMTP blocking), subsystems
      (fast load, RAB, VNET, Docker compat, ipset, GRE, remote block lists),
      and logging (log file, log drops, trim, recent entries)
[New] --lookup HOST: check if host exists in trust files (allow, deny, global
      allow, global deny) without searching iptables/ipset rules; exits 0 if
      found, 1 if not found
[New] -h/--help: explicit help handler exits 0; previously no args exited 1
[New] --validate/--check: validate config without starting firewall
[New] --list-allow/--list-deny (--la/--ld): display trust file entries with
      comments and blank lines stripped
[New] --dump-config: self-documenting alias for -o/--ovars
[New] snapshot_save(): atomic fast load snapshot writes via mktemp+mv;
      validates iptables-save exit code and output; IPv6 snapshot failure
      non-fatal to IPv4; backend marker tracking for nft/legacy compatibility
[New] Ban expiry: structured addedtime=EPOCH markers in permanent trust
      entries for reliable expiry; backward-compatible with pre-2.0.2 entries
[New] uninstall.sh: removes all system-wide artifacts; prompts before
      removing install directory and logs
[New] install.sh: post-install dependency warnings for iptables, ip,
      modprobe; non-fatal for chroot/container builds
[New] install.sh: auto-detect default network interface on fresh install;
      show interface and listening port details during install and upgrade
[New] install.sh: auto-detect and disable conflicting firewall services
      (firewalld, ufw) during installation; check_deps() runtime warning
      when conflict detected post-install; CentOS 6 safe (no systemctl)
[New] IPT_LOCK_SUPPORT="auto": auto-detect iptables -w lock support at
      startup by probing iptables --help; CentOS 6 (1.4.7, no -w) safely
      resolves to disabled; explicit "0"/"1" still honored; .ca.def
      preamble defaults to "auto" for fresh installs and pre-2.0.1 upgrades
[New] DOCKER_COMPAT="auto": auto-detect container runtimes at startup by
      checking for DOCKER-USER chain in iptables filter table; resolves to
      "1" when Docker/Podman/containerd is actively managing iptables, "0"
      otherwise; explicit "0"/"1" still honored; zero overhead when forced

  -- Bug Fixes --

[Fix] install.sh: fix directory permissions (find-based dirs=750, files=640),
      suppress vnetgen stderr, verify source files before install, remove
      unsafe pre-install rm -rf
[Fix] importconf: guard vnet/*.rules glob, suppress stderr, fix
      INSTALL_PATH default, preserve custom files and hook permissions
      during upgrade
[Fix] importconf: migrate EG_DROP_CMD from space-separated to
      comma-separated format in root and extras importconf
[Fix] Anchor grep/sed patterns across trust, expiry, and block escalation
      functions to prevent IP substring collisions; escape dots in IP
      addresses, use exact-match flags
[Fix] cli_trust_remove(): spec-based iptables rule deletion with removal
      tracking; anchored comment cleanup; reject empty argument
[Fix] lgate_mac(): use $VF_LGATE instead of undefined $LGATE_MAC; gateway
      MAC filtering was non-functional
[Fix] expirebans(): fix $ip loop variable shadowing global iproute2 path;
      replace unquoted array expansion with IFS read; add date parse error
      handling; skip ttl= entries; fix orphaned comment cleanup
[Fix] expirebans()/expire_temp_entries()/flush_temp_entries(): defer
      cli_trust_remove calls until after iteration to avoid modifying trust
      files while reading
[Fix] ipset_migrate_rules(): add 5-field (v2.0.1) to 7-field migration;
      5-field entries were silently dropped on upgrade
[Fix] glob_allow_download()/glob_deny_download(): validate entries with
      valid_host() instead of raw file copy
[Fix] SMTP_BLK: add chain-exists guard for VNET re-sourcing; add to Docker
      compat flush chain list; warn on empty SMTP_PORTS
[Fix] .ca.def: add missing preamble defaults for SYSCTL_CONNTRACK_*,
      DOCKER_COMPAT, IG_ICMPV6_TYPES, EG_ICMPV6_TYPES; preserve DLIST_*_URL
      customizations on upgrade
[Fix] Fast load: validate snapshots before iptables-restore; flush partial
      rules on restore failure; check firewall exit code to prevent saving
      broken state; skip snapshot save on failure
[Fix] Unknown CLI options now exit with code 1 instead of 0
[Fix] Quote shell variables in iptables command context, dot-source paths,
      and config references across apf, firewall, functions.apf, sysctl.rules,
      internals.conf, and apf.init
[Fix] Strip control characters from trust comment field to prevent line
      injection in allow/deny hosts files
[Fix] refresh(): populate REFRESH_TEMP from trust files instead of
      iptables-save parsing; move temp file creation past MD5 early-exit;
      exit 0 when trust rules unchanged
[Fix] flush(): remove /etc/cron.d/refresh.apf on firewall stop; prevents
      refresh into a stopped firewall
[Fix] Cron lifecycle: clean runtime-created refresh.apf and apf_develmode
      cron entries during install and uninstall
[Fix] Rename head() to apf_banner() to stop shadowing /usr/bin/head; add
      "v2" qualifier to GPL notice
[Fix] Propagate cli_trust/cli_trust_temp return codes to CLI exit status;
      apf -a/-d/-ta/-td now exit 1 on failure
[Fix] REFRESH_TEMP now protects bare IPv6 trust entries during refresh;
      change case filter from *:* to *=* so IPv6 addresses are not excluded
[Fix] Install FLOW document to doc/ directory alongside README
[Fix] cl_cports(): reset EG_DROP_CMD, SMTP, and connlimit variables between
      VNET iterations to prevent rule leaking
[Fix] Preserve file inodes: logrotate copytruncate directive for external
      tail -f consumers; trim() uses cat+rm instead of mv
[Fix] Shell compatibility: revert bash 4.2+ case conversion for CentOS 6;
      replace deprecated -a test operator; add -r flag to read commands
[Fix] Local variable hygiene: add missing local declarations to 10+
      functions; hoist declarations out of loops; avoid modifying globals
[Fix] Temp file hygiene: use mktemp for all temp files; register with
      _apf_reg_tmp for signal-safe cleanup across apf, uninstall.sh,
      trim(), and list()
[Fix] sysctl.rules: fix wrong proc paths for secure_redirects,
      send_redirects, and proxy_arp; per-interface sysctls require conf/all/
      prefix — settings were silently never applied
[Fix] Redirect user-facing error messages to stderr across cli_trust(),
      cli_trust_remove(), cli_trust_temp(), trust_lookup(), search(), and
      apf startup
[Fix] list(): check $EDITOR env var before hardcoded editor list; fall back
      to pager when no editor found
[Fix] --ipset-update: add informational message when USE_IPSET=0
[Fix] --gre-up/--gre-down: report disabled state instead of silently exiting
[Fix] install.sh: replace hardcoded /sbin/chkconfig with command -v discovery
[Fix] bandmin(): replace hardcoded /usr/local/bandmin with command -v
      discovery
[Fix] help(): add missing -st alias to status line help text
[Fix] trim(): exclude blank lines from data line count
[Fix] vnetgen: strip Docker @ifN suffix from ip link output in
      SET_ADDIFACE block; prevents duplicate VNET rules in containers
[Fix] internals.conf: initialize IPT_FLAGS="" before conditional append
      to prevent environment variable contamination
[Fix] .ca.def: add missing preamble defaults for IPT_LOCK_SUPPORT and
      IPT_LOCK_TIMEOUT; prevents unset variables on upgrade from pre-2.0.1

  -- Changes --

[Change] trust_hosts(): batch bare host rules via iptables-restore --noflush;
      reduces per-trust-file lock acquisitions from O(n) to O(1); advanced
      syntax entries still use individual iptables calls via trust_entry_rule()
[Change] File-based flock mutex: replace FD-based exec/flock with file-based
      gate; noclobber + PID fallback; EXIT trap releases lock on signal;
      trust CLI operations acquire lock for cron race prevention
[Change] ESTABLISHED,RELATED state tracking moved earlier in INPUT chain;
      established connections now fast-path past VNET, port filtering, and
      logging
[Change] Fast load uptime threshold raised from 5 to 10 minutes
[Change] Consolidate 3 cron files into single cron.d.apf with daily restart,
      hourly ipset refresh, and per-minute temp expiry
[Change] ipset batch loading via ipset restore; reduces load time from
      minutes to seconds for large block lists
[Change] Performance: replace subprocess chains with bash builtins across
      all hot paths; modernize string tests; remove unnecessary wrappers
[Change] VNET: replace fork-heavy parsing with builtins and glob patterns;
      fix ifconfig detection; add variable quoting
[Change] help(): show readable option names over cryptic aliases; add
      --rules, --info, --lookup; hide silent aliases from display
[Change] Drop Ubuntu 22.04 from CI matrix; redundant with 20.04+24.04
[Change] trust_hosts(): replace four-pass grep cascade with single-pass loop
      delegating advanced syntax to trust_entry_rule(); anchor comment filter;
      eliminate fragile protocol-substring classification
[Change] importconf: clarify message on same-version reinstall
[Change] install.sh: optimize sed path replacement with grep -rl pre-filter;
      add error handling
[Change] Code consolidation: extract shared helpers across trust, ipset, port
      filtering, and firewall subsystems; remove dead variables
[Change] bt.rules: unify IPv4/IPv6 sanity, fragment, and pzero chain
      creation via parameterized helpers; extract _log_drop() and _rab_log()
      for consistent LOG+DROP patterns
[Change] cports: extract port-filter and uid-filter loop helpers; consolidate
      EGF guards; define NDP_TYPES constant
[Change] Extract inline regex patterns to named variables in validation
      functions for portability
[Change] vnetgen: replace for-in-$(cmd) anti-patterns with while-read loops
[Change] download_url(): log TLS diagnostic hint on download failure for
      legacy system troubleshooting
[Change] nft backend detection: extract detect_ipt_backend() to eliminate
      duplicated iptables --version parsing
[Change] conf.apf: split TCR_PASS and TCR_PORTS onto separate lines for
      readability; aligns with .ca.def template
[Change] Runtime file permissions: align chmod 600 to 640 for trust files
      and log file created at runtime; matches install.sh convention
[Change] cli_trust_temp(): extract _maybe_block_escalate() helper to replace
      4 repeated inline block-escalation blocks

